name: Mommy n Me Home Daycare
detail:
First, I would like to tell you a little bit about myself and my family.  I have always lived in the Kansas City area, growing up in Olathe.  I got married to my husband seven years ago, he brought into the family a wonderful little girl who is 9 years old.  Together, my husband and I have two children --- our daughter is 7 years old and our son is 15 months old.  We are blessed to have such a healthy and happy family!  In addition to our three children, we have two very friendly dogs, Kado and Maggie.  They are big to children, but do not be scared, they are harmless and well behaved!  Our "daycare home" has its own 700+ sqft of dedicated play area, so your child will not be located in the same room as the dogs.  Along with all the chaos, we have 38 gallons of aquatic life living within the walls of the "daycare home"!  The children love to watch the variety of marine life swimming before their eyes!  Please rest assured, our home is VERY clean and tidy...I promise! 

I am fully trained in CPR and First Aid.  This is a licensed daycare home located in Gardner, Kansas.

I have an educational background in child psychology and early childhood education.  Upon your request, I would be more than happy to elaborate in detail pertaining to my college background, as well as the numerous training opportunities that I have been priviledge to be a part of.

My philosophy is simple.  I want to help guide children by giving them a nurturing, safe environment to flourish and “just be kids.”  I emphasize manners, kindness, and caring on a daily basis.  For younger children, I know that physical contact is important for a sense of security and for older children, that same sense of security comes from learning to communicate and understand their needs.  I get down to the children’s level when we play and take more of a teaching role when we’re learning.  I believe children are a true gift and I enjoy every moment my life overlaps with that of a child.  Please rest assured that the children in my care are my utmost priority.

Open channels of communication are very important for me to have with all the parents.  I fully understand that there are different parenting styles and will do what I can to fulfill the needs of you and your child.  I offer many different ways to communicate any feedback, concerns, or issues you may have.  Feel free to speak to me directly in person, over the phone, email or just write a note.  Nothing is too big or too small when it comes to your child. 

I am looking forward to many milestones with you and your child!

name: New Beginnings Childcare Daycare Home
detail:
Bright Beginnings located in Manhattan Kansas is a Nationally Accredited Montessori inspired pre-school program.  It was established January 1999 by Donna Moody who specializes in Early Childhood Education, working with children between the ages of 3-6.  Bright Beginnings strives to create a welcoming but orderly space for your children that allows them to work and play freely.  The order a Montessori classroom creates encourages children to become self disciplined and independent.

The purpose of Montessori  Education is to cultivate the child's natural desire to learn.  In the Montessori classroom this objective is approached in two ways: first, by allowing each child to experience the excitement of learning by their own choice rather than being forced; and second, by helping them to perfect their natural tools for learning, so that their ability will be at maximum in future learning situations.  The Montessori materials have a dual long-range purpose in addition to their immediate purpose of giving specific information to the child.

A Montessori school is a unique cycle of learning designed to take advantage of a child's sensitive years between three and six, when they can absorb information from an enriched environment.  A child who acquires the basic skills of reading and arithmetic in this natural way has the advantage of beginning her education without drudgery, boredom, or discouragement. By pursuing the child's individual interests in a Montessori classroom, they gain an early enthusiasm for learning, which is the key to them becoming a truly educated person.

name: Community Action Head Start Hudson A
detail:
Head Start,launched in 1964, was designed to help break the cycle of poverty facing preschool children in low-income families. Today, Head Start is a comprehensive child
development program available to income-eligible families at no cost. Community Action Head start provides home-based, center-based, and family child care xperiences for children. As a combined Early Head Start and Head Start program, services
are available for prenatal women, infants and children through kindergarten age. In Kansas, children are eligible for kindergarten the year they become five years old, on or before August 31. Early Head Start services; for prenatal women and children through age 3, on or before August 31; are available through Community Action program for families throughout Shawnee County. Head Start services; for preschool children ages 3 or 4, on or before August 31; are available through Community Action program for families in the eastern portion of USD 501 Topeka Public Schools and the
Shawnee County portions of USD 437 Auburn-Washburn School District, USD 345 Seaman School District, and USD 450 Shawnee Heights School District.

detail:

CCC serves 78 children, ages 3-5 in the Lawrence community.

Extended hours and days may be available for working families.
ECKAN Head Start promotes health development for all children.  In order for the program and the child’s family to be certain a child is healthy, a variety of screenings must be completed. name: Heritage Christian Academy
detail:
We invite you to join us at Heritage Christian Academy as we seek to glorify God by teaching and modeling Christ-like character while providing academic excellence within a caring community.  The information we  provide here is an overview of our high quality, biblically-based  academic program, but we  strongly suggest that you schedule a visit to the school. While on campus, you’ll experience for yourself the joy that loving, professional educators can bring when the totality of what is taught is grounded in the truth of God’s Word.

Heritage Christian Academy offers PreSchool four mornings a week (Monday through Thursday) with a variety of schedule options and full-day Kindergarten. We also offer an After Care program (until 5:30 PM) on all full days of school. Our elementary curriculum provides strong concentration in core subjects as well as weekly special classes in Art, Music, Phys Ed and Spanish. Our updated Media Center offers many computer and library opportunities while our expanded instrumental band program for fifth and sixth graders provides another artistic outlet.

Heritage Christian Academy’s Junior/Senior High offers an excellent well-rounded education rooted in biblical truth for students in seventh through twelfth grades. Heritage Christian Academy’s ultimate goal is to graduate students who are prepared academically and spiritually to be a light in their community, to understand the nature of God, His Word, and are committed to the importance of impacting the world for Christ.
